Machimia albula is a moth in the family Depressariidae. It was described by Turner in 1946. It is found in Australia, where it has been recorded from Queensland.The wingspan is 16â€“17 mm. The forewings are whitish-grey with fuscous markings and a dot on the base of the costa, as well as a subbasal curved line of three dots. There is a small spot on two-thirds of the costa, connected by an outwardly curved line, as well as two subapical costal dots and a dotted terminal line. The hindwings are whitish.